<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>Merchant - Account Setup & Verification</title>
        <link href="css/theme.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/global.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/merchant_account_setup.css">
        <style>/* Basic reset for preview consistency */body { margin: 0; padding: 0; font-family: sans-serif; }</style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="mas-layout">
            <!-- Sidebar Overlay (mobile) -->
            <div id="sidebarOverlay" class="sidebar-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <!-- Sidebar -->
            <aside id="masSidebar" class="mas-sidebar" role="navigation" aria-label="Merchant documentation navigation">
                <div class="sidebar-section">
                    <div class="sidebar-section-label">Getting Started</div>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_docs_home" onclick="load_page('merchant_docs_home')"> <i class="fa fa-home"></i> Overview </a>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_getting_started" onclick="load_page('merchant_getting_started')"> <i class="fa fa-rocket"></i> Getting Started </a>
                    <a class="sidebar-link active" data-page="merchant_account_setup" onclick="load_page('merchant_account_setup')"> <i class="fa fa-user-check"></i> Account Setup </a>
                </div>
                <div class="sidebar-section">
                    <div class="sidebar-section-label">Payments</div>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_qr_payments" onclick="load_page('merchant_qr_payments')"> <i class="fa fa-qrcode"></i> QR Code Payments </a>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_nfc_payments" onclick="load_page('merchant_nfc_payments')"> <i class="fa fa-wifi"></i> NFC Payments </a>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_transactions" onclick="load_page('merchant_transactions')"> <i class="fa fa-exchange-alt"></i> Transactions </a>
                </div>
                <div class="sidebar-section">
                    <div class="sidebar-section-label">Configuration</div>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_settings" onclick="load_page('merchant_settings')"> <i class="fa fa-cog"></i> Settings </a>
                </div>
                <div class="sidebar-section">
                    <div class="sidebar-section-label">Support</div>
                    <a class="sidebar-link" data-page="merchant_troubleshooting" onclick="load_page('merchant_troubleshooting')"> <i class="fa fa-life-ring"></i> Troubleshooting </a>
                </div>
            </aside>
            <!-- Main Content Area -->
            <div class="mas-main">
                <div class="mas-content-wrapper">
                    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
                    <nav class="mas-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                        <a href="#" onclick="load_page('landing_page'); return false;">Docs</a>
                        <span class="separator"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
                        <a href="#" onclick="load_page('merchant_docs_home'); return false;">Merchant</a>
                        <span class="separator"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
                        <span class="current">Account Setup</span>
                    </nav>
                    <!-- Page Title -->
                    <h1 class="mas-page-title" id="page-title">Account Setup & Verification</h1>
                    <p class="mas-page-subtitle">
        Complete guide to registering your merchant account, completing KYC verification, setting up your business profile, and linking your bank account for seamless payment settlements. </p>
                    <!-- Registration Process Section -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="registration">
                        <h2>Registration Process</h2>
                        <p>
          Creating your MPay Network merchant account is a straightforward process. Follow the steps below to get started with accepting payments from your customers. </p>
                        <div class="steps-container">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Download the MPay Merchant App</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Download the MPay Merchant Wallet from the <strong>Google Play Store</strong> or <strong>Apple App Store</strong>. Search for "MPay Merchant" and look for the official app with the verified badge.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Create Your Account</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Open the app and tap <strong>"Create Merchant Account"</strong>. Enter your business email address and create a strong password. You'll receive a verification code via email.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Verify Your Email</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Enter the 6-digit verification code sent to your email. The code expires in 10 minutes. If you don't receive it, check your spam folder or request a new code.
</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Set Up Two-Factor Authentication</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    For security, you'll be prompted to set up 2FA using your phone number. Enter your mobile number and verify it with the SMS code. This is <strong>mandatory</strong> for all merchant accounts.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">5</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Accept Terms of Service</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Review and accept the MPay Merchant Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. Your account will be created in a <span class="inline-code">pending_verification</span> state until KYC is completed.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="callout info">
                            <div class="callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout-content">
                                <div class="callout-title">Note</div>
                                <div class="callout-text">You can explore the app interface and configure settings while your verification is pending, but you won't be able to accept payments until KYC verification is complete.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Account Statuses</h3>
                        <p>Your merchant account will go through the following status transitions during the setup process:</p>
                        <div class="doc-table-container">
                            <table class="doc-table">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Status</th>
                                        <th>Description</th>
                                        <th>Can Accept Payments</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><span class="inline-code">pending_verification</span></td>
                                        <td>Account created, KYC not yet submitted</td>
                                        <td><i class="fa fa-times" style="color: #ef4444;"></i> No</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><span class="inline-code">under_review</span></td>
                                        <td>KYC documents submitted, awaiting review</td>
                                        <td><i class="fa fa-times" style="color: #ef4444;"></i> No</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><span class="inline-code">verified</span></td>
                                        <td>KYC approved, account fully active</td>
                                        <td><i class="fa fa-check" style="color: #22c55e;"></i> Yes</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><span class="inline-code">suspended</span></td>
                                        <td>Account suspended for review or policy violation</td>
                                        <td><i class="fa fa-times" style="color: #ef4444;"></i> No</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- KYC Verification Section -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="kyc-verification">
                        <h2>KYC Verification</h2>
                        <p>
          Know Your Customer (KYC) verification is required by financial regulations to ensure the security and legitimacy of all merchant accounts on the MPay Network. This process typically takes <strong>1–3 business days</strong>. </p>
                        <h3>Required Documents</h3>
                        <p>Prepare the following documents before starting the verification process:</p>
                        <div class="requirement-card">
                            <div class="requirement-card-header">
                                <div class="requirement-card-icon blue">
                                    <i class="fa fa-id-card"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card-title">Government-Issued Photo ID</div>
                                <span class="status-badge required">Required</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="requirement-card-desc">
                                Valid passport, national ID card, or driver's license. The document must be unexpired and clearly show your full name, photo, and date of birth. Both front and back images are required for ID cards.
</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="requirement-card">
                            <div class="requirement-card-header">
                                <div class="requirement-card-icon green">
                                    <i class="fa fa-building"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card-title">Business Registration Certificate</div>
                                <span class="status-badge required">Required</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="requirement-card-desc">
                                Official business registration document issued by your local authority. This should include the registered business name, registration number, and date of incorporation.
</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="requirement-card">
                            <div class="requirement-card-header">
                                <div class="requirement-card-icon amber">
                                    <i class="fa fa-file-invoice"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card-title">Tax Identification Number (TIN)</div>
                                <span class="status-badge required">Required</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="requirement-card-desc">
                                Your business tax identification number or certificate. This is used for regulatory compliance and settlement reporting.
</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="requirement-card">
                            <div class="requirement-card-header">
                                <div class="requirement-card-icon purple">
                                    <i class="fa fa-map-marker-alt"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card-title">Proof of Business Address</div>
                                <span class="status-badge optional">Optional</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="requirement-card-desc">
                                A utility bill, bank statement, or lease agreement dated within the last 3 months showing your business address. Required if your business address differs from the registration certificate.
</div>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Verification Process</h3>
                        <p>Here's what to expect during the KYC verification:</p>
                        <div class="verification-timeline">
                            <div class="vt-step">
                                <div class="vt-dot">
                                    <i class="fa fa-upload"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="vt-content">
                                    <h4>Document Upload</h4>
                                    <p>Upload clear, high-resolution photos or scans of all required documents through the app. Accepted formats: JPG, PNG, PDF. Max file size: 10MB per document.</p>
                                    <div class="vt-time">
                                        <i class="fa fa-clock"></i> ~5 minutes
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="vt-step">
                                <div class="vt-dot">
                                    <i class="fa fa-camera"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="vt-content">
                                    <h4>Selfie Verification</h4>
                                    <p>Take a live selfie within the app for facial recognition matching against your photo ID. Ensure good lighting and remove any head coverings (unless worn for religious reasons).</p>
                                    <div class="vt-time">
                                        <i class="fa fa-clock"></i> ~2 minutes
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="vt-step">
                                <div class="vt-dot">
                                    <i class="fa fa-search"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="vt-content">
                                    <h4>Automated Review</h4>
                                    <p>Our system performs initial checks on document authenticity, facial matching, and data extraction. Most automated checks complete within minutes.</p>
                                    <div class="vt-time">
                                        <i class="fa fa-clock"></i> ~15 minutes
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="vt-step">
                                <div class="vt-dot">
                                    <i class="fa fa-user-shield"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="vt-content">
                                    <h4>Manual Review</h4>
                                    <p>A compliance team member reviews your documents for final approval. You may be contacted if additional information is needed.</p>
                                    <div class="vt-time">
                                        <i class="fa fa-clock"></i> 1–3 business days
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="vt-step completed">
                                <div class="vt-dot">
                                    <i class="fa fa-check"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="vt-content">
                                    <h4>Verification Complete</h4>
                                    <p>Once approved, your account status changes to <span class="inline-code">verified</span> and you'll receive a confirmation email. You can now start accepting payments!</p>
                                    <div class="vt-time">
                                        <i class="fa fa-check-circle" style="color:#22c55e;"></i> Account ready
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="callout warning">
                            <div class="callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout-content">
                                <div class="callout-title">Important</div>
                                <div class="callout-text">If your KYC verification is rejected, you'll receive an email explaining the reason. Common reasons include blurry document images, expired documents, or mismatched information. You can resubmit your documents up to 3 times before needing to contact support.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Business Profile Setup Section -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="business-profile">
                        <h2>Business Profile Setup</h2>
                        <p>
          Your business profile is what your customers see when they make a payment. Setting it up correctly builds trust and ensures smooth transactions. </p>
                        <h3>Profile Information</h3>
                        <p>Navigate to <strong>Settings → Business Profile</strong> in the merchant app to configure the following:</p>
                        <div class="doc-table-container">
                            <table class="doc-table">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Field</th>
                                        <th>Description</th>
                                        <th>Status</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Business Name</strong></td>
                                        <td>Your official business or trade name. Displayed on customer receipts and payment confirmations.</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge required">Required</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Business Category</strong></td>
                                        <td>Select from categories: Retail, Food & Beverage, Services, Healthcare, Education, etc.</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge required">Required</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Business Address</strong></td>
                                        <td>Physical address of your business location. Used for location-based features.</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge required">Required</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Business Logo</strong></td>
                                        <td>Square image, minimum 256×256px. PNG or JPG format. Max 5MB.</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge optional">Optional</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Contact Phone</strong></td>
                                        <td>Customer-facing phone number for your business.</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge optional">Optional</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Business Description</strong></td>
                                        <td>Brief description of your business (up to 250 characters).</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge optional">Optional</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Website URL</strong></td>
                                        <td>Your business website or social media page.</td>
                                        <td><span class="status-badge optional">Optional</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Uploading Your Business Logo</h3>
                        <p>A professional logo helps customers identify your business. Follow these specifications:</p>
                        <ul class="doc-list">
                            <li>Minimum dimensions: <strong>256×256 pixels</strong> (recommended: 512×512)
                            </li>
                            <li>Aspect ratio: <strong>1:1</strong> (square)
                            </li>
                            <li>File format: PNG (preferred for transparency) or JPG</li>
                            <li>Maximum file size: <strong>5MB</strong>
                            </li>
                            <li>Background: Solid color or transparent recommended</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-block-header">
                                <span class="code-block-lang">API Reference</span>
                                <button class="code-copy-btn" aria-label="Copy code">
                                    <i class="fa fa-copy"></i> Copy
                                </button>
                            </div>
                            <pre><code>PUT /api/v1/merchant/profile
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

{
  "business_name": "Coffee Bean Co.",
  "category": "food_beverage",
  "address": {
    "street": "123 Main Street",
    "city": "Metro City",
    "state": "MC",
    "postal_code": "10001",
    "country": "US"
  },
  "phone": "+1-555-0123",
  "description": "Premium artisan coffee shop",
  "logo": [binary file data]
}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="callout success">
                            <div class="callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout-content">
                                <div class="callout-title">Tip</div>
                                <div class="callout-text">You can update your business profile at any time. Changes to the business name may require additional verification and could take up to 24 hours to reflect.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Bank Account Linking Section -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="bank-linking">
                        <h2>Bank Account Linking</h2>
                        <p>
          Link your bank account to receive payment settlements. All funds collected through MPay will be transferred to your linked bank account based on your settlement schedule. </p>
                        <h3>How to Link Your Bank Account</h3>
                        <div class="steps-container">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Navigate to Bank Settings</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Open the merchant app and go to <strong>Settings → Bank Accounts → Add Bank Account</strong>.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Enter Bank Details</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Enter your bank name, account holder name, account number, and routing/SWIFT code. Ensure the account holder name matches your KYC-verified name or business name.
</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Micro-Deposit Verification</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    We'll send two small test deposits (under $0.50 each) to your bank account. This typically takes 1–2 business days. You'll need to confirm the exact amounts to verify ownership.
</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                                <div class="step-title">Confirm and Activate</div>
                                <div class="step-description">
                                    Once you've confirmed the micro-deposit amounts, your bank account will be verified and set as your default settlement account.
</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Settlement Schedule</h3>
                        <p>Choose from the following settlement frequencies:</p>
                        <div class="doc-table-container">
                            <table class="doc-table">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Schedule</th>
                                        <th>Description</th>
                                        <th>Cut-off Time</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Daily (T+1)</strong></td>
                                        <td>Funds settled to your bank the next business day</td>
                                        <td>11:59 PM UTC</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Weekly</strong></td>
                                        <td>All transactions settled every Monday</td>
                                        <td>Sunday 11:59 PM UTC</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Bi-Weekly</strong></td>
                                        <td>Settlements processed every other Monday</td>
                                        <td>Alternate Sunday 11:59 PM UTC</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Monthly</strong></td>
                                        <td>All transactions settled on the 1st of each month</td>
                                        <td>Last day of month, 11:59 PM UTC</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                        <div class="callout danger">
                            <div class="callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout-content">
                                <div class="callout-title">Security Warning</div>
                                <div class="callout-text">Never share your bank account details or MPay login credentials with anyone. MPay support will <strong>never</strong> ask for your password or full bank account number via email, phone, or chat.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Managing Multiple Bank Accounts</h3>
                        <p>
          You can link up to <strong>3 bank accounts</strong> to your merchant profile. However, only one account can be set as the primary settlement account at any time. To switch your primary account: </p>
                        <ul class="doc-list">
                            <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Bank Accounts</strong>
                            </li>
                            <li>Tap the bank account you want to make primary</li>
                            <li>Select <strong>"Set as Primary"</strong>
                            </li>
                            <li>Confirm with your 2FA code</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>
                    <!-- FAQ Section -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="faq">
                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                        <p>Common questions about merchant account setup and verification.</p>
                        <div class="faq-container">
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-1">
                                    <span class="faq-question-text">How long does KYC verification take?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-1" role="region">
                                    <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                                        <p>KYC verification typically takes <strong>1–3 business days</strong>. The automated review completes within minutes, but the manual compliance review may take longer depending on volume. You'll receive an email notification once your verification is complete.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-2">
                                    <span class="faq-question-text">What if my KYC verification is rejected?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-2" role="region">
                                    <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                                        <p>If your verification is rejected, you'll receive an email explaining the specific reason. Common reasons include blurry images, expired documents, or name mismatches. You can resubmit your documents up to 3 times. After 3 attempts, please contact our support team for assistance.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-3">
                                    <span class="faq-question-text">Can I use a personal bank account for settlements?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-3" role="region">
                                    <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                                        <p>For sole proprietorships, you may use a personal bank account as long as the account holder name matches your KYC-verified identity. For registered businesses (LLC, Corporation, etc.), you must use a business bank account in the name of the registered entity.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-4">
                                    <span class="faq-question-text">How do I update my business information after verification?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-4" role="region">
                                    <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                                        <p>Most profile fields (description, logo, phone, website) can be updated at any time through <strong>Settings → Business Profile</strong>. However, changes to your business name, registration number, or registered address will require additional verification and may take 1–2 business days to approve.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-5">
                                    <span class="faq-question-text">Is my data secure during the KYC process?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-5" role="region">
                                    <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                                        <p>Absolutely. All documents are encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3) and at rest (AES-256). Your KYC data is stored in compliance with PCI DSS Level 1 standards and applicable data protection regulations. We retain documents only for the legally required period and securely delete them thereafter.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-6">
                                    <span class="faq-question-text">Can I change my settlement schedule later?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-6" role="region">
                                    <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                                        <p>Yes, you can change your settlement schedule at any time from <strong>Settings → Bank Accounts → Settlement Schedule</strong>. Changes take effect starting from the next settlement cycle. Any pending settlement for the current cycle will be processed under the previous schedule.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
